\begin{document}$$ {\text{J}}_{{\text{v}}}  = {\text{L}}_{{\text{p}}}  \times {\text{S}} \times {\left[ {{\left( {{\text{P}}_{{\text{c}}}  - {\text{P}}_{{\text{i}}} } \right)} - \sigma  \times {\left( {\Pi _{{\text{c}}}  - \Pi _{{\text{i}}} } \right)}} \right]} $$\end{document}where Jv is the trans-capillary flux of fluid, Lp the hydraulic conductivity of capillaries, S the exchange surface, Pc and Pi the hydrostatic pressure of the capillary and interstitium, respectively, σ the reflection coefficient of proteins across the capillary wall, and Πc and Πi the oncotic pressure in the capillaries and interstitium, respectively.
